item.title: Fall TV 2014 winners and losers
item.ExtractedText: << Previous Â Next >> Loser: The Thanksgiving holiday was a downer for fans of Fox's "Red Band Society." The new fall dramedy about a pediatric hospital ward has tried to survive its unimpressive ratings, but Fox has halted production on future episodes beyond its original 13-episode order. The series will air two more episodes before being removed from Fox's lineup in early December. Here's a look at the other winners and losers of the fall 2014 TV season so far.
